The percentage of European population exposed to levels higher than the regulatory limits is about 7–8% for NO
 2, 6–8% for PM
 2.5, 13–19% for PM
 10 and 12–29% for O
 3 (
 EEA, 2019). Premature deaths due to acute respiratory diseases from such pollutants are estimated to be over to two million per year worldwide and 45.000 for Italy (
 Brunekreef and Holgate, 2002; 
 Huang et al., 2016; 
 EAA, 2019; 
 Watts et al., 2019).
